Mythic

Game Overview
	Mythic is a worker placement, double push y/our luck, set collection game set in the 1920â€™s.
	In Mythic you play as a member of the Society of Explorers and Xploration, searching dangerous locations with your team of researchers to find clues that allow you to make a claim as to the existence of Bigfoot before other players make their claims.

Components
21 Unique Explorer Cards
35 Research Team Member Cards
5 Location Boards
125-150 Evidence Cards
10 Bigfoot [TPK] Cards
5 Skills Reference Card
4 Explorer Meeples

Setup
1) Place the location boards at the center of the table
2) Each player recieves an Explorer Meeple and a unique Explorer Card
3) Deal each player their corresponding color's Scavenger, Recon and Research Expert research team member cards. 
Alternatively, for advanced play each player selects the three research team member cards of their color that they want for their team and return the rest to the box.
4) Locate and separate out each of the seeded cards 
Each seeded deck is made up of nine cards related to the locations evidence type and the following cards;
3 twos, 2 threes, 1 two with a sighting, 1 golden evidence and 2 TPKS
5) Place all the seeded decks on their corresponding locations and add 16-21 evidence cards into each locations evidence pile and shuffle them all together
6) Begin play at the planning phase with the player who last read a scientific study.

Gameplay Flow
1) Assigning research team members to either a location or to stay at camp.
2) Use three opportunities to either explore to gain evidence -or- activate traits
3) Return to camp with all retrieved evidence -or- research team member goes MIA
4) Make claim based on evidence in different categories
5) Repeat process from step 1 above

Game Phases
Planning Phase- during this phase players in turn order assign one of their research team member cards at a time to a location or to stay home until all members are assigned. 
By assigning their research team member card to a location board in the 1,2,3 or 4 spot the player is showing an intent to explore the location
By keeping their research member card back the player is showing they intend to remove that member from harms way and to perform an opportunity.

Explore Phase- during this phase players in turn order select a location where they have at least one research team member card and then players resolve all of the opportunities of each research team member in the order of their location spots.
Players have three opportunities alloted to each team member on the location, they may either spend a number of opportunities to activate the given research team member's trait and/or may explore the top card of the evidence deck once per opportunity spent.
To explore players may reveal the top card of the evidence from their location's evidence pile and place it on top of their research team member. 
If the player ever has two bigfoot tags amongst their searched evidence cards then their searching research team member goes MIA. To go MIA return your research member card to your play area and flip it face down.
If a research team member goes MIA place the evidence they found faceup back onto the location in the lost evidence pile.
If any player reveals an evidence card with a large bigfoot symbol this represents a a total party kill and everyone on the location becomes MIA and no evidence is collected. [Survivors collect retains one evidence and recieves an eyewitness evidence card].
Once all research team members have used all of their opportunities at the loaction, if your research team member is still alive then return your research team member card and any evidence they discovered to your play area.
Once all location boards with research team members on them have been resolved move on to the next phase.

Lay Claim- Players may Lay Claim if they have enough evidence to do so, if someone does there is one more full round for all other players (see the Laying Claim section for more information)
If no players Lay Claim then repeat the game phases starting with the planning phase, starting with the next player clockwise from this round's starting player.

Card Types
Explorers [dissect the parts of a card]
 Name
 Survivor and Search and Rescue
 Two fields of study that boost corresponding evidence points at game's end.
Research Team Members
 Name
 Trait
 Research Team color
Evidence
